   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1834_06_30_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#New-Burlington-Street_ENK"/>New Burlington Street
                  <date when="1834-06-30">June 30. 1834</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>Madam</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>As I shall shortly approach the<lb/>
               sale of the number of copies which would <choice>
                  <orig>au-<lb/>
               thorize</orig>
                  <reg>authorize</reg>
               </choice> me to transmit to you a further<lb/>
               promissory note for the contingent £200 <choice>
                  <orig>con-<lb/>
               templated</orig>
                  <reg>contemplated</reg>
               </choice> in the agreement for the first<lb/>
               Edition of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">"Helen"</title>, I beg to say that I am<lb/>
               ready to transmit such promissory note<lb/>
               by post to you if you please, or to hand the<lb/>
               same to any agent in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName>. whom you<lb/>
               may authorize to <del>you</del> receive it<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>As I trust that you will consider that<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1834_06_30_page02.jpg"/>
            </p>
            <p>the publication of their Work has, in my hands,<lb/>
               been followed up with zeal and activity, and<lb/>
               that your own wishes have been punctually<lb/>
               fulfilled, may I take occasion to say that I<lb/>
               shall be most happy to be entrusted by<lb/>
               you with the publication of the story<lb/>
               called <title ref="./Workography.xml#Grant1">"Granting for granted,"</title> to which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">Mr<lb/>
               Lockhart</persName> alluded when I had the <choice>
                  <orig>plea-<lb/>
               sure</orig>
                  <reg>pleasure</reg>
               </choice> of negotiating with him for <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">"Helen"</title>
               <lb/>
               and to solicit the favor of you acquainting<lb/>
               me at what time you intend to give your<lb/>
               next novel to the World<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I have the honor to be,<lb/>
               Madam,<lb/>
               with great respect,<lb/>
               Your most <choice>
                  <orig>obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>obedient</reg>
               </choice> servant,<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">Richard Bentley</persName>..<lb/>
            </closer>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1834_06_30_page03.jpg"/>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworth Town</placeName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>1834</addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Bently</persName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
                  <addrLine>about <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title>
                  </addrLine>
                  <lb/>
               </address>
            </closer>
